# Echothink-Patch: 0001-branding
# Title: Set user-visible product identity to Echothink Browser
# Area: branding
# Depends-On: none
# Browser-Layer-Reason: The product name is compiled into the browser binary's localized string resources and the local first-run WebUI; it cannot be supplied by an Echothink backend service. This is browser-shell identity, not business logic.
# Preferred-Surface-Checked: native-required (IDS_PRODUCT_NAME / IDS_SHORT_PRODUCT_NAME are GRIT string resources with no policy/preference/extension override; the first-run identity strings live in the inherited local WebUI source)
# Security-Critical-Areas: none
# Native-Files-Touched: chrome/app/chromium_strings.grd, chrome/browser/ui/webui/ungoogled_first_run.h
# Rebase-Risk: low (chromium_strings.grd IDS_PRODUCT_NAME block is long-term stable); medium for ungoogled_first_run.h because it depends on the inherited patches/extra/ungoogled-chromium/first-run-page.patch having already created the file
# Validation: Apply inherited patches, then this patch with `patch -p1`; build and confirm About/chrome://version and chrome://ungoogled-first-run show "Echothink Browser" while Chromium/Ungoogled Chromium credits and license links remain.
#
# Scope notes:
# - Updates only the smallest stable user-visible product-identity insertion
#   points. IDS_PRODUCT_NAME and IDS_SHORT_PRODUCT_NAME propagate the product
#   name across menus, the About settings surface, and chrome://version.
# - Updates the inherited first-run page title and heading to the Echothink
#   identity while deliberately preserving the upstream attribution sentence
#   ("built with ungoogled-chromium patches ... default Chromium experience")
#   and all upstream links. Credits and license generation (add-credits.patch,
#   licenses.py output, root LICENSE) are untouched.
# - Deliberately does NOT touch chrome/app/theme/chromium/BRANDING or other
#   low-level executable/installer identifiers. Windows packaging identity and
#   executable naming are deferred to T30/T31 per the branding inventory.

--- a/chrome/app/chromium_strings.grd
+++ b/chrome/app/chromium_strings.grd
@@ -294,9 +294,9 @@
         </then>
         <else>
           <message name="IDS_PRODUCT_NAME" desc="The Chrome application name" translateable="false">
-            Chromium
+            Echothink Browser
           </message>
           <message name="IDS_SHORT_PRODUCT_NAME" desc="The Chrome application short name." translateable="false">
-            Chromium
+            Echothink Browser
           </message>
         </else>
--- a/chrome/browser/ui/webui/ungoogled_first_run.h
+++ b/chrome/browser/ui/webui/ungoogled_first_run.h
@@ -25,7 +25,7 @@
                         const content::WebContents::Getter& wc_getter,
                         GotDataCallback callback) {
     std::string source = R"(
-<title>ungoogled-chromium first run page</title>
+<title>Echothink Browser first run page</title>
 <meta name="color-scheme" content="light dark">
 <style>
  @import url(chrome://resources/css/text_defaults_md.css);
@@ -47,7 +47,7 @@
 </style>
 <base target="_blank">
 <section>
- <h2>ungoogled-chromium</h2><p>
+ <h2>Echothink Browser</h2><p>
  This browser was built with ungoogled-chromium patches and differs from the default Chromium experience
  in a few ways. Look over the sections below and the
  <a href="https://github.com/ungoogled-software/ungoogled-chromium/blob/master/docs/default_settings.md">
